text=(:title Wolf-Blooded Character Creation Guidelines :)%0a[[#wbtop]]%0a[[GameRef.Wolf-BloodedCharacterCreation?action=edit|Click here to Edit]]%0a%0a(:table border=0 style=float width=40%25 align=right  cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr align=center:)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a(:cellnr bgcolor=#996600 align=center:)%0a'''Contents'''%0a(:cellnr:) %0a*[[#Creation| Character Creation]]%0a*[[#Restricted| Restricted]]%0a*[[#ixp| Incentive XP]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a[[#Creation]]%0a[++'''Character Creation'''++]%0a%0aWolf-Blooded characters are created like ordinary mortals, allowing the following notes to apply:%0a%0a*Use the scaling Wolf-Blooded Merit in ''Blood of the Wolf (pg.126)''. The Merit '''Wolf-Blooded''' costs no restricted slots up to level 4. '''Wolf-Blooded 5''' costs just one restricted slot.%0a%0a*Wolf-Blooded may ''not'' be Second Sighters anymore.%0a%0a*However, Wolf-Blooded may take certain Merits from the ''Book of Spirits'' on a Restricted basis, requiring case-by-case approval.%0a%0a*Wolf-Blooded may learn '''Spirit Tongue (•••)''' (Pg 90 Book of Spirits), perfectly. A%0ahuman’s mouth and tongue are literally incapable of capturing the nuances of this otherworldly language.  This Merit, however, at least allows a human to make a go at it. The character with this Merit can express very simple ideas (one to three-word phrases) without any roll.  More complex communication requires a Manipulation + Expression roll. This roll may suffer negative dice modifiers (maximum of –5 dice) if the circumstances are tense or if the ideas communicated are based solely in human experience (i.e., spirits would have a difficult time comprehending the idea much less the language involved).%0a%0a*The '''Watched''' Merit represents a NPC Werewolf, and thus needs to be discussed with the ST team. You don't need this Merit to represent PC Werewolves who are watching over your Wolf-Blooded.%0a%0a[--%25color=#996600%25[[#wbtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a[[#Restricted]]%0a[++'''Restricted'''++]%0a%0a* Wolf-Blooded that are members of certain Wolf-Blooded Families may be allowed the opportunity to become Skinchangers. This is reserved for characters that prove themselves to influential werewolves with the ability to teach these special rituals.%0a[--%25color=#996600%25[[#wbtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a[[#ixp]]%0a[++'''Incentive XP'''++]%0a%0a[--%25color=#996600%25[[#wbtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.WerewolfNavigationBar :)
